{"type":"message","id":"11a7a0d3","parentId":"453fb809","timestamp":"2026-03-06T01:35:07.242Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking about the status of x402 pay-as-you-go implementation for Parse agents. This is a specialist task involving code, APIs, and payment integration. According to my routing protocol in AGENTS.md, this should go to temujin (Code, builds, bugs, APIs, deploy, design, architecture, payment, protocol, SDK).\n\nBut first, I should check if there's any existing context about this. Let me check the memory files and any relevant project status.\n\nActually, let me first read the kurultai-router skill to make sure I route correctly, then route to temujin for the actual status check and response.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Let me check the current status of the x402 implementation for Parse."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_61c3fbbd9c7e4da5997bf1ac","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/main/memory/2026-03-05.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_82592d9233754722a4df223b","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/main/shared-context/ARCHITECTURE.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":66,"output":206,"cacheRead":19136,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":19408,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772760895183}}
{"type":"message","id":"6294aa05","parentId":"11a7a0d3","timestamp":"2026-03-06T01:35:07.279Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_61c3fbbd9c7e4da5997bf1ac","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 2026-03-05 - main Activity Log\n\n## Auto-initialized by Jochi Analysis\n\n### 00:09 - System Online\n- Agent operational\n- Monitoring active\n\n### 04:02 - Hourly Kurultai Reflection\n**Status:** Complete\n\n**Agent Reflections:**\n- Temujin: Rule T4 added, flagged Parse Conversion Alert\n- Mongke: New self-scheduling rule M1 (generate research when idle >30min)\n- Chagatai: New self-scheduling rule C1 (audit docs when idle)\n- Jochi: New self-pull rule J1, identified stale queue task\n- Ogedei: Grade F, Rule O1 not followed, fleet-wide idle identified\n\n**Key Findings:**\n1. Fleet-wide idle pattern (0/6 agents active)\n2. Parse Conversion Alert Check failing (now runs but returns null metrics)\n3. Stale queue task closed (error spike resolved)\n\n**Actions Taken:**\n- Closed stale Jochi task `normal-1772691220.md` (error spike from 01:13 resolved)\n- Ran Parse Conversion Alert Check manually - script works but all metrics are null\n- Reflection report saved to `logs/reflections/2026-03-05-0402-hourly-reflection.md`\n\n**New Rules Committed:**\n| Agent | Rule | Trigger |\n|-------|------|---------|\n| Mongke | M1 | idle >30min → generate research |\n| Chagatai | C1 | idle + healthy → audit docs |\n| Jochi | J1 | queue >0 + idle >30min → pull task |\n| Ogedei | O1 | idle >15min + blocked items → fix |\n| Temujin | T4 | (invocation triggers needed) |\n\n**Parse Conversion Alert Issue:**\n- Script runs successfully but all funnel metrics return null\n- Database connection works (Railway proxy)\n- Likely a data/query issue, not script crash\n- Previous 525s hang was likely DB timeout\n\n### 17:00 - Parse for Agents Milestone\n**Major Achievement:** Parse for Agents feature is now production-ready\n\n**Accomplishments:**\n1. **Fixed Task Execution Path Bug:**\n   - watchdog-gather.sh, heartbeat-task-executor.py, task-watcher.py\n   - All agents now properly execute tasks from their queues\n\n2. **Created parse-skill:**\n   - Location: ~/.openclaw/agents/main/skills/parse-skill/\n   - Agents can now use Parse for Agents API to evaluate AI outputs\n   - SKILL.md and test_skill.md created\n\n3. **Parse for Agents Test Success:**\n   - Tested with GPT-4o Mini via OpenRouter\n   - Quality score: 98/100\n   - Google OAuth working (sign in as Kublai Kurultai)\n\n4. **Production Ready:**\n   - Parse for Agents feature deployed and functional\n   - Ready for customer use\n\n### 17:10 - Parse-Skill OpenRouter Integration\n**Task Dispatched:** Update parse-skill to use OpenRouter for customer tests\n\n**Requirement:**\n- When customers execute the skill, test must run with same exact model they're using\n- OpenRouter API key provided for this purpose\n\n**Status:**\n- ACP session spawned: `agent:claude:acp:afe67817-60b5-4f36-b6a9-f6cb3d04581a`\n- Task: Modify parse-skill to use OpenRouter with customer's model\n\n### 17:57 - x402 Payment Design (Horde-Brainstorming)\n**Task:** Design payment system for Parse for Agents using x402 protocol\n**Method:** /horde-brainstorming (diverge/evaluate/converge)\n\n**Outcome:**\n- Complete design document created: `projects/parse-for-agents/x402-payment-design.md`\n- Pricing model: Tiered per-call with USDC on Base L2\n- Price range: $0.005 - $0.15 per call depending on depth\n- SDK: @x402/hono (direct fit for our framework)\n- Status: DESIGN COMPLETE - Ready for implementation\n\n### 17:58 - Claude Code Instructions Generalization\n**Task:** Create generalized Claude Code instructions for all agents\n**Created:** `shared-context/CLAUDE-CODE-INSTRUCTIONS.md`\n**Contents:**\n- Default session configuration (effort: high, thinking: enabled)\n- Horde skills reference (planning, implementation, quality)\n- Session spawn template\n- Agent-specific defaults\n- Best practices\n\n### 18:01 - Deep Reflection (Hour 18)\n**Infrastructure:** Gateway ✓, Parse 200 ✓, LLM Survivor 200 ✓\n**Agent Health:** No stuck subagents, no CRITICAL escalations\n**ACP Sessions:** x402 design completed, parse-skill update completed\n**Fleet Status:** Idle (5/6 agents have empty queues)\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772760907267}}
